    "<h1 align=\"center\">MS Structure Solving</h1>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "93b7d0d6-6f07-4f57-a1ef-df7cf0d48d53",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "<h2 >Stellar Equations</h2>\n",
    "<h5>Density</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{d\\rho}{dr}= - \\dfrac{\\left( \\dfrac{GM\\rho}{r^2} + \\dfrac{\\partial P}{\\partial T} \\dfrac{dT}{dr} \\right)}{\\dfrac{\\partial P}{\\partial \\rho}}$$\n",
    "<h5>Temperature</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dT}{dr}= - min \\left(\\dfrac{3\\kappa\\rho L}{16\\pi a c T^3 r^2}, \\left(1-\\dfrac{1}{\\gamma}\\right)\\dfrac{T}{P} \\dfrac{GM\\rho}{r^2}\\right)$$\n",
    "<h5>Mass</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dM}{dr} = 4 \\pi r^2 \\rho $$\n",
    "<h5>Luminosity</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dL}{dr} = 4 \\pi r^2 \\rho \\varepsilon$$\n",
    "<h5>Tau</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{d\\tau}{dr} = \\kappa \\rho$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "571f1a88-f004-4a61-81b9-141f062c2c20",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<h2 >Dark Matter Heating Equations</h2>\n",
    "<h5>Distribution</h5>\n",
    "<h6>for some power $s$ and normalization $\\rho_{DM,0}$</h6>\n",
    "$$\\rho_{DM} = \\rho_{DM,0}\\left( \\dfrac{r}{1 pc}\\right)^{-s}$$\n",
    "<h5>Power Density</h5>\n",
    "$$\\mathcal{P}=\\sigma_{DM}\\upsilon_{DM} \\left(\\dfrac{\\rho_{DM}(r)}{m_{DM}} \\right)^2 m_{DM} c^2$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "896d85ee-b23f-48ee-89b7-dbb498a6f859",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<h2 >Dark Matter Heating Effects</h2>\n",
    "<h5> 1) Dark Matter impact on luminosity: $\\dfrac{dL}{dr}$</h5>\n",
    "<h5>total energy generation</h5>\n",
    "$$\\epsilon_{DM}(r) = \\dfrac{\\mathcal{P}}{\\rho} = \\dfrac{\\sigma_{DM}\\upsilon_{DM}}{\\rho (r)} \\dfrac{\\rho_{DM}(r)}{m_DM}^2 m_{DM}c^2$$\n",
    "$$= \\dfrac{\\sigma_{DM}\\upsilon_{DM}c^2}{m_{DM}\\rho (r)}\\left(\\rho_{DM,0}\\left(\\dfrac{r}{1pc}\\right)^{-5}\\right)^2$$\n",
    "<h5>As $r$ increases $\\epsilon_{DM}$ should decrease</h5>\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dL}{dr}=4 \\pi r^2 \\rho\\varepsilon = \\dfrac{dM}{dr} \\varepsilon$$\n",
    "<h5>The luminosity of a star comes from converting the stellar mass to energy using $\\varepsilon$, so the luminosity from dark matter annihilation should come from the mass of dark matter<h5>\n",
    "<h5>The mass of dark matter is</h5>\n",
    "$$m_{DM}=\\int_0^r \\rho_{DM}4\\pi r^2 \\: \\mathrm{d}r \\implies \\dfrac{dm_{DM}}{dr}=4\\pi r^2 \\rho_{DM}$$ \n",
    "<h5>So the luminosity from the dark matter annihilation is<h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dL_{DM}}{dr}=\\dfrac{dm_{DM}}{dr}\\varepsilon_{DM}$$\n",
    "$$=4\\pi r^2\\rho_{DM}\\dfrac{\\mathcal{P}}{\\rho_{DM}}$$\n",
    "$$=4\\pi r^2 \\mathcal{P}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\implies \\dfrac{dL}{dr}=4\\pi r^2 \\rho_{star} \\left(\\varepsilon_{pp}+\\varepsilon_{CNO}\\right)+4\\pi r^2 \\mathcal{P}$$\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dL}{dr}=4\\pi r^2 \\left( \\rho \\left( \\varepsilon_{pp} + \\varepsilon_{CNO} \\right) + \\mathcal{P}\\right)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "<h5>2) Dark Matter impact on temperature gradient: $\\dfrac{dT}{dr}$</h5>\n",
    "$$\\dfrac{dT}{dr}\\sim \\dfrac{-3\\kappa \\rho L}{16\\pi a c T^3 r^2}$$\n",
    "\n"
   ]
